Dialogue: 0,2:51:19.63,2:51:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,罗伯特汤普森爵士\N{\rEng}''Sir Robert Thompson...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:22.73,2:51:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,曾在马来半岛  击败共产党游击队\N{\rEng}who led the victory over Communist guerillas in Malaya...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:26.10,2:51:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,他现在是  兰德公司（美军智库）的顾问\N{\rEng}is now a RAND corporation consultant...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:29.11,2:51:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,最近回到越南\N{\rEng}recently returned to Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,2:51:31.72,2:51:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,向尼克松总统报告形势\N{\rEng}to sound out the situation for President Nixon.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:34.45,2:51:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,上周  他告诉总统\N{\rEng}He told the president last week...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:36.15,2:51:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,情况大有好转\N{\rEng}that things felt much better...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:39.22,2:51:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,以后会更好\N{\rEng}and smelled much better over there.''
Dialogue: 0,2:51:44.14,2:51:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么想  大兵？\N{\rEng}How do they smell to you, soldier?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:58.42,2:52:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你会自由  会有人看管你\N{\rEng}You'll be free. You'll be under guard.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:02.02,2:52:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,闲暇时读读这些\N{\rEng}Read these at your leisure.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:04.59,2:52:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,别弄丢了\N{\rEng}Don't lose them.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:06.33,2:52:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,别想逃  会打死你\N{\rEng}Don't try to escape. You'll be shot.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:10.37,2:52:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们回头可以谈谈这些\N{\rEng}We can talk of these things later.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:31.06,2:55:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是空心人\N{\rEng}''We are the hollow men.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:34.43,2:55:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是稻草人\N{\rEng}We are the stuffed men...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:36.47,2:55:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,依靠在一起  脑壳中装满了稻草\N{\rEng}leaning together at peace fiIlled with straw.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:43.48,2:55:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我们干巴的嗓音\N{\rEng}Alas, our dried voices
Dialogue: 0,2:55:44.61,2:55:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们在一块儿窃窃低语时\N{\rEng}when we whisper together...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:45.95,2:55:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,寂静又毫无意义\N{\rEng}are quiet and meaningless as wind in dry grass...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:47.71,2:55:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,好似干草地上的风\N{\rEng}or a rat's feet over broken glass in a dry cellar.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:50.65,2:55:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,或我们干燥的地窖中\N{\rEng}He's really out there.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:55.02,2:55:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他真在那\N{\rEng}He is really there.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:56.49,2:55:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,成形却没有形式\N{\rEng}Shape without form...
Dialogue: 0,2:55:59.79,2:56:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,成影却没有颜色\N{\rEng}shade without color...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:02.36,2:56:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,力量瘫痪\N{\rEng}paralyzed force...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:05.50,2:56:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,有姿势却无动作\N{\rEng}gesture without motion.''
Dialogue: 0,2:56:07.30,2:56:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道他在说什么吗？\N{\rEng}Do you know what the man's saying?
Dialogue: 0,2:56:10.10,2:56:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗？\N{\rEng}Do you?
Dialogue: 0,2:56:12.37,2:56:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这是辩证法\N{\rEng}This is dialectics.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:13.79,2:56:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,非常简单的辩证法\N{\rEng}It's very simple dialectics.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:15.41,2:56:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,就像从1到9  没有或许\N{\rEng}It's one through nine. No maybes,
Dialogue: 0,2:56:17.17,2:56:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,没有假设  没有分数\N{\rEng}no supposes, no fractions.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:19.18,2:56:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能在太空漫游\N{\rEng}You can't travel in space.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:20.46,2:56:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能进入太空\N{\rEng}You can't go out into space, you know...
Dialogue: 0,2:56:21.91,2:56:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,要是没有分数的话\N{\rEng}without like, you know, with fractions.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:24.68,2:56:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你要在哪着陆？  1/4？ 3/8？\N{\rEng}What are you gonna land on? One-quarter? Three-eighths?
Dialogue: 0,2:56:27.19,2:56:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,若从这去金星  你要做什么？\N{\rEng}What are you gonna do when you go from here to Venus?
Dialogue: 0,2:56:29.46,2:56:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这是辩证物理学  对吗？\N{\rEng}That's dialectic physics, okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:31.42,2:56:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,辩证逻辑认为非爱即恨\N{\rEng}Dialectic logic is, there's only love and hate.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:33.69,2:56:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你要么爱人  要么恨人\N{\rEng}You either love somebody or you hate 'em.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:36.43,2:56:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,蠢货！\N{\rEng}Mutt!
Dialogue: 0,2:56:39.60,2:56:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你这蠢货\N{\rEng}You mutt.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:41.47,2:56:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是这该死的世界  结束的方式\N{\rEng}This is the way the fucking world is.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:44.80,2:56:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,看看我们这鬼地方\N{\rEng}Look at this fucking shit we're in, man!
Dialogue: 0,2:56:47.34,2:56:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,并非一声巨响  而是一阵呜咽\N{\rEng}Not with a bang. A whimper.
Dialogue: 0,2:56:49.31,2:56:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,伴随这阵呜咽\N{\rEng}And with a whimper,
Dialogue: 0,2:56:51.16,2:56:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我他妈闪了  杰克\N{\rEng}I'm fucking splitting,Jack.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:21.67,2:57:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,在河上\N{\rEng}On the river,
Dialogue: 0,2:57:22.99,2:57:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在那一刻  我看着他\N{\rEng}I thought that the minute I looked at him...
Dialogue: 0,2:57:24.44,2:57:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我会知道要做什么\N{\rEng}I'd know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:27.18,2:57:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,结果并非如此\N{\rEng}But it didn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:30.38,2:57:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我和他在一起好几天\N{\rEng}I was in there with him for days.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:33.02,2:57:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,没有守卫\N{\rEng}Not under guard.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:34.75,2:57:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我是自由的\N{\rEng}I was free.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:37.12,2:57:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但他知道我哪也不会去\N{\rEng}But he knew I wasn't going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:40.36,2:57:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我要做什么  他比我还清楚\N{\rEng}He knew more about what I was going to do than I did.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:51.04,2:57:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,若老川的将军们  看见这一情景\N{\rEng}If the generals backin Nha Trang could see what I saw...
Dialogue: 0,2:57:55.37,2:57:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,仍想让我杀了他吗？\N{\rEng}would they still want me to kill him?
Dialogue: 0,2:57:59.41,2:58:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,或许更为急切\N{\rEng}More than ever, probably.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:02.41,2:58:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,若他的家人知道\N{\rEng}And what would his people back home want
Dialogue: 0,2:58:03.78,2:58:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他已经离他们有多遥远时\N{\rEng}if they ever learned...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:05.35,2:58:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会怎么想？\N{\rEng}just how far from them he'd really gone?
Dialogue: 0,2:58:10.12,2:58:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他跟他们决裂了\N{\rEng}He broke from them...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:12.12,2:58:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,然后  跟自己也决裂了\N{\rEng}and then he broke from himself.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:15.19,2:58:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没见一个人  被如此的隔绝\N{\rEng}I'd never seen a man so broken up and...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:18.46,2:58:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,和撕裂\N{\rEng}ripped apart.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:20.43,2:58:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我看见了恐怖\N{\rEng}I've seen the horrors--
Dialogue: 0,2:58:23.24,2:58:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你见过的恐怖\N{\rEng}horrors that you've seen.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:27.27,2:58:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你无权称我是凶手\N{\rEng}But you have no right to call me a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:29.48,2:58:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你有权杀我\N{\rEng}You have a right to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:32.54,2:58:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你有这个权力\N{\rEng}You have a right to do that.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:36.65,2:58:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,但你无权审判我\N{\rEng}But you have no right to judge me.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:45.66,2:58:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,对于那些\N{\rEng}It's impossible for words...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:49.56,2:58:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道什么叫恐怖的人\N{\rEng}to describe...
Dialogue: 0,2:58:52.00,2:58:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,来说\N{\rEng}what is necessary
Dialogue: 0,2:58:58.54,2:59:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,无法用语言\N{\rEng}to those
Dialogue: 0,2:59:01.04,2:59:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,向他们描述\N{\rEng}who do not know
Dialogue: 0,2:59:03.64,2:59:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,什么是必需的\N{\rEng}what horror means.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:08.81,2:59:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,恐怖\N{\rEng}Horror.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:13.12,2:59:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,恐怖有张面孔\N{\rEng}Horror has a face.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:18.12,2:59:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须与之结交\N{\rEng}And you must make a friend of horror.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:21.73,2:59:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,恐怖与道德恐怖\N{\rEng}Horror and moral terror...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:25.66,2:59:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,应是你的朋友\N{\rEng}are your friends.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:27.23,2:59:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不是\N{\rEng}If they are not...
Dialogue: 0,2:59:29.67,2:59:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那他们便是  你应惧怕的敌人\N{\rEng}then they are enemies to be feared.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:33.57,2:59:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是真正的敌人\N{\rEng}They are truly enemies.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:40.51,2:59:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得在特种部队的日子\N{\rEng}I remember when I was with Special Forces.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:47.89,2:59:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎是千百年前的事了\N{\rEng}Seems a thousand centuries ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:55.33,2:59:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我们进了一个营地\N{\rEng}We went into a camp to inoculate...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:00.33,3:00:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,给一些孩子打预防针\N{\rEng}some children.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:05.80,3:00:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,替他们注射完  预防小儿麻痹的疫苗后\N{\rEng}We'd left the camp...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:08.61,3:00:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们离开了营地\N{\rEng}after we had inoculated the children for polio.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:13.75,3:00:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这个老人\N{\rEng}And this old man came running after us,
Dialogue: 0,3:00:15.01,3:00:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们后面边跑边哭\N{\rEng}and he was crying.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:16.42,3:00:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他看不见\N{\rEng}He couldn't say.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:20.75,3:00:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们回去时\N{\rEng}We went back there...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:23.06,3:00:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他们已经来过了  砍掉了\N{\rEng}and they had come and hacked off...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:26.86,3:00:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,所有接种过的手臂\N{\rEng}every inoculated arm.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:31.06,3:00:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,它们堆成了一堆\N{\rEng}There they were, in a pile--
Dialogue: 0,3:00:33.47,3:00:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,一堆\N{\rEng}a pile of...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:36.87,3:00:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,小小的手臂\N{\rEng}little arms.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:40.11,3:00:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得\N{\rEng}And I remember...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:44.38,3:00:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我哭了  像一些老大娘般\N{\rEng}I-I--I cried.I wept like...
Dialogue: 0,3:00:51.05,3:00:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,抹眼泪\N{\rEng}some grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:55.99,3:00:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我咬牙切齿\N{\rEng}I wanted to tear my teeth out.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:58.27,3:01:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道自己想干什么\N{\rEng}I didn't know what I wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:01.06,3:01:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我要记着这一幕  永不忘记\N{\rEng}And I want to remember it. I never want to forget it.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:04.30,3:01:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,永不忘记\N{\rEng}I never want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:07.67,3:01:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我顿悟\N{\rEng}And then I realized...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:10.94,3:01:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,如同中弹\N{\rEng}like I was shot--
Dialogue: 0,3:01:12.80,3:01:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,如同一颗钻石般  坚硬的子弹\N{\rEng}like I was shot with a diamond--
Dialogue: 0,3:01:16.28,3:01:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,正中我的前额\N{\rEng}a diamond bullet right through my forehead.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:21.45,3:01:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,于是我想  天哪  真是天才\N{\rEng}And I thought, ''My God, the genius of that.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:25.45,3:01:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,天才\N{\rEng}The genius.''
Dialogue: 0,3:01:28.05,3:01:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,这么干的决心\N{\rEng}The will to do that.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:32.19,3:01:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,完美  真实 彻底 清晰 纯粹\N{\rEng}Perfect, genuine, complete, crystalline, pure.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:39.23,3:01:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,然后  我明白了\N{\rEng}And then I realized...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:40.97,3:01:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他们比我强悍  因为他们受得了\N{\rEng}they were stronger than me because they could stand it.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:44.97,3:01:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这些人并非怪物  他们是人\N{\rEng}These were not monsters. These were men--
Dialogue: 0,3:01:47.64,3:01:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,受过训练的骨干\N{\rEng}trained cadres.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:50.28,3:01:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他们用心作战\N{\rEng}These men who fought with their hearts...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:52.98,3:01:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他们有家庭  子女\N{\rEng}who have families, who have children...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:55.11,3:01:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,心中充满了爱\N{\rEng}who are fiIlled with love...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:57.22,3:02:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们有力量\N{\rEng}that they had the strength--
Dialogue: 0,3:02:00.62,3:02:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,有这样做的\N{\rEng}the strength...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:06.16,3:02:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,力量\N{\rEng}to do that.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:08.23,3:02:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,若我有十师的这号人马\N{\rEng}If I had ten divisions of those men...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:13.57,3:02:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这里的麻烦很快便会摆平\N{\rEng}then our troubles here would be over very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:18.40,3:02:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你的部下必须\N{\rEng}You have to have men...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:21.91,3:02:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,有道德观\N{\rEng}who are moral...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:25.04,3:02:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,同时也能\N{\rEng}and at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:30.65,3:02:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,利用他们的\N{\rEng}who are able to...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:34.92,3:02:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,原始本能去杀人\N{\rEng}utilize their primordial instincts to kill...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:38.86,3:02:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,不带感情  不会激动\N{\rEng}without feeling, without passion...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:43.03,3:02:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不去判断是非\N{\rEng}without judgment--without judgment.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:50.94,3:02:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,因为正是判断令我们落败\N{\rEng}Because it's judgment that defeats us.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:13.09,3:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我担心我儿子\N{\rEng}I worry that my son...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:16.33,3:03:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,也许不明白我的用意\N{\rEng}might not understand what I've tried to be.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:22.63,3:03:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,若我被杀  威尔德\N{\rEng}And if I were to be killed, Willard...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:28.97,3:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望有人去我家\N{\rEng}I would want someone to go to my home...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:31.98,3:03:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我儿子这一切\N{\rEng}and tell my son everything.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:37.58,3:03:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我所做的和你看到的一切\N{\rEng}Everything I did. Everything you saw.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:42.19,3:03:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,因为最令我厌恶的\N{\rEng}Because there's nothing that I detest more than...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:45.82,3:03:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,莫过于谎言的恶臭了\N{\rEng}the stench of lies.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:50.93,3:03:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你理解我  威尔德\N{\rEng}And if you understand me, Willard, you--
Dialogue: 0,3:03:55.93,3:03:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你会为我作这件事的\N{\rEng}you will do this for me.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:04.40,3:05:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,街霸  这是  全能  完毕\N{\rEng}PBRStreet Gang, this is Almighty. Over.
